<h2 id="photographers-identities-catalog">Photographers’ Identities Catalog</h2>

<p>Photographers’ Identities Catalog (PIC) is a growing collection of biographical data describing photographers, studios, manufacturers, and others involved in the production of photographic images in the last 175 years. Each entry consists of a Name, Nationality, Date(s), and Sources from which the entry was derived. Where known, they also include at least some of the following: gender, role (if other than Photographer), photographic processes and formats used, locations (of birth, death, studio addresses, or areas of activity) and their corresponding dates, and known repositories of their work. PIC is an increasingly thorough resource for the attribution and dating of photographs, and hopefully of interest to broader historical and genealogical communities, as well. The information has been culled from trusted biographical dictionaries, catalogs and databases, and from extensive original research by NYPL Photography Collection staff.</p>



