<h3 id="identify-and-date-your-photographs">Identify and date your photographs</h3>

<p>Have old family photographs you’re trying to date? Many studio portraits, such as Cabinet Cards or Cartes de Visite print the photographer’s or studio’s name and address along the bottom or on the back of the photo. In many cases, PIC has the dates a studio occupied a specific address. For instance, William Watson Washburn operated a studio at 26 Camp Street, New Orleans from 1849-1853. After that he moved to 120 Canal Street.</p>



